# ── Dependencies (Phase 2-A, Session #18) ──────────────────────────────
# The published site is dependency-free Vanilla JS. node_modules is only the
# local install of the pinned dev tools (eslint/stylelint/playwright/http-server).
# It is reproducible from package-lock.json via `npm ci` and must never be committed.
node_modules/
npm-debug.log*

# ── Python bytecode caches ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generated by running the .github/scripts/*.py checkers locally. Not source.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]

# ── Playwright local artifacts (baselines are produced/committed via CI) ──
/test-results/
/playwright-report/
/blob-report/
/playwright/.cache/

# ── OS / editor noise ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp

# ── Claude Code (CLI agent) local/personal config ──────────────────────
# .claude/settings.json (project, committed = team-shared) and .claude/commands/
# ARE tracked. Only the per-machine personal override is ignored. Claude Code
# also auto-ignores this file when it first creates it; this entry is explicit
# so the intent is clear in source control.
.claude/settings.local.json
# Local-only Claude memory (personal context, never shared)
CLAUDE.local.md
# Session-local scheduled-task lock (auto-managed by Claude Code; never share)
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# ── Private source documents (NEVER commit) ────────────────────────────
# Personal/confidential source material (resume, career history, offer letters,
# employer-provided documents) is dropped at the repo root ONLY as local input
# for generating abstracted, privacy-safe evidence (docs/evidence/*). The shipped
# repo is Vanilla JS/MD with NO legitimate .pdf/.docx, so these patterns are a
# safe blanket guard against committing any such source doc. Re-identification /
# 身バレ防止: the originals are processed locally then deleted; only ABSTRACTED
# claims (ranges, role types, deliverable types — no company/client/project names)
# are ever committed. Check 122 machine-enforces that no office/document/archive
# format (pdf/docx/.../zip/...) is ever tracked. Images (png/jpg/webp) are excluded
# (legitimately used: webp asset / playwright baselines).
*.pdf
*.docx
*.doc
*.xlsx
*.pptx
# Office / document formats (no legitimate repo use — could carry contract/proposal/minutes content)
*.rtf
*.odt
*.ods
*.odp
*.pages
*.key
*.numbers
*.csv
# Archives (could bundle private documents)
*.zip
*.7z
*.rar
*.tar
*.gz
*.tgz
